<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE STATE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A skull found by a hiker near the Lafayette-Orinda border has prompted an 
investigation into whether it is that of murder victim Luis Reyna, whose 
headless body was found in the same area last year, Contra Costa County 
sheriff's officials said. Reyna, a popular waterfront commissioner, disappeared 
July 18, the same day he told family members he was going to meet commission 
colleague Enrique Zambrano, who vanished the same day as Reyna. Zambrano had 
been charged with the attempted murder of a UC Berkeley professor and his wife 
early last year. 
</P>
