<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST: LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
1,700 IN SANTA CLARITA VALLEY LOSE POWER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
About 1,700 Santa Clarita Valley residents were without electricity Saturday 
night after an underground cable failed, a Southern California Edison spokesman 
said. 
</P>
<P>
The power outage at 7:45 p.m. hit homes around Tournament Road and Player Drive 
near the Vista Valencia Golf Course in Valencia, said Rosalie Gnam, Santa 
Clarita Valley manager for Edison. The cable, estimated to be 15 years old, 
"just gave way," she said. 
</P>
<P>
Within two hours, power had been restored to about three-fourths of the 
residents. The rest had electricity by 1 a.m., Gnam said. 
</P>
<P>
Crews worked throughout the night to repair the cable, she said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
