<P>
SPOON-WIELDING HOUSTON MAN WOUNDED BY OFFICER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
HOUSTON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A police officer, unable to see what was in the hands of a man who earlier had 
threatened his wife with a knife, shot and wounded the suspect Sunday as he 
came at him with a spoon, authorities said. The suspect, Andras Santana, 50, 
was in critical condition after being shot once in the chest by an officer 
identified as C. Murphy, police said. 
