<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY DIGEST: LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
MODJESKA CANYON; 
</P>
<P>
MOTORCYCLIST KILLED IN COLLISION WITH CAR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A motorcyclist was killed on a curving canyon road when he crossed into 
oncoming traffic and collided with a car, the California Highway Patrol said 
Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
Randal Ross, 25, of Riverside was fatally injured when he was thrown from his 
motorcycle about 4:40 p.m. Saturday, CHP dispatcher Joe David said. 
</P>
<P>
Ross, who was wearing a helmet, was traveling about 50 m.p.h. on Modjeska Grade 
Road, east of Santiago Canyon Road, in the hilly area north of O'Neil Regional 
Park. He failed to negotiate a curve and crossed into the eastbound lanes, 
David said. The motorcyclist collided with a 1987 Honda Accord traveling about 
15 m.p.h. that was driven by Henry McFalls, 66, of El Toro, the CHP said. 
</P>
<P>
McFalls was not injured. The collision is being investigated, David said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
