<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY DIGEST: LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
NEWPORT BEACH; 
</P>
<P>
MAN HURT BODYSURFING AT CRYSTAL COVE PARK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A man in his 40s who injured his neck and back while bodysurfing at Crystal 
Cove State Park on Sunday was reported in serious condition at Hoag Hospital. 
</P>
<P>
The victim's identity, age and residence could not be immediately learned 
"because he was unconscious when he was brought to shore," said a lifeguard. 
</P>
<P>
According to a County Fire Department spokesman, the man was seen floating and 
obviously injured in the surf about 1 p.m. The accident took place off the 
cliff-lined park, which is between Newport Beach and Laguna Beach. 
</P>
<P>
The man was airlifted to Hoag Hospital by a Marine Corps helicopter. 
</P>
</TEXT>
