<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
PETERS, BUNCH POWER TITANS TO 7-3 VICTORY OVER GONZAGA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Rex Peters and Paul Bunch hit home runs to lead Cal State Fullerton to a 7-3 
victory over Gonzaga Sunday in a nonconference baseball game at Titan Field. 
</P>
<P>
Peters' two-run home run in the fifth inning gave Fullerton (17-6) a 5-2 lead. 
The homer extended his hitting steak to 23 games. Peters, a senior from Orange 
Coast College, is hitting .360 (31 of 86) and leads the team with 12 doubles. 
</P>
<P>
Bunch, a junior outfielder from Cypress College, hit an opposite-field home run 
off the scoreboard in right-center to give Fullerton a 1-0 lead in the second 
inning. Huck Flener (6-0) pitched the first five innings for the victory. James 
Popoff pitched the ninth for the save. 
</P>
<P>
In nonconference men's tennis: 
</P>
<P>
UC Irvine 6, Clemson 3 -- Irvine's Mark Kaplan, the 72nd-ranked player in the 
nation, defeated No. 7 ranked John Sullivan, 6-2, 6-2, at Irvine. It was the 
13th consecutive victory for Kaplan, who has won 10 sets in a row. Irvine 
(12-5) is ranked fourth. Clemson (13-5) is ranked 10th. 
</P>
<P>
In nonconference softball: 
</P>
<P>
Cal State Fullerton 8, Northwestern 3 -- Fullerton (19-4) scored three runs in 
the first and led, 7-0, before Northwestern scored three runs in the sixth. 
</P>
<P>
Cal Sate Fullerton 2, Iowa 0 -- Ann Van Dortrecht (8-2) pitched a two-hitter. 
</P>
<P>
In nonconference men's volleyball: 
</P>
<P>
Ohio State 3, UC Irvine 2 -- Visiting Ohio State won, 15-6, 6-15, 15-6, 1-15, 
15-12. Ohio State is 3-9; Irvine 5-21. 
</P>
