<P>
SOUTHLAND; 
</P>
<P>
PLEASURE FAIRE FINDS A HOME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and wire service reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The San Bernardino County Board of Supervisors unanimously voted today to 
approve holding the Renaissance Pleasure Faire this spring in the county's Glen 
Helen Regional Park, 55 miles from downtown Los Angeles. 
</P>
<P>
The event will take place on the 1,425-acre site for seven consecutive weekends 
beginning May 13, organizers said. The park, northwest of the City of San 
Bernardino, is south of the intersection of Interstates 15 and 215. 
</P>
<P>
Forced to find a new location after its longtime site in Agoura was purchased 
by a developer, the Faire had attempted to move to eastern Ventura County. But 
organizers withdrew their application after residents objected to the increased 
traffic the event would bring. 
</P>
