<HEADLINE>
<P>
NIBBLES AND BITS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Chapman College in Orange will present honorary Doctor of Humane Letters 
degrees to Frank Capra and James Stewart during its commencement exercises May 
28. Stewart, who will be 81 on May 20, plans to attending and accept on behalf 
of Capra, who will turn 92 on May 18. "We consider it a privilege to honor two 
gentlemen whose lives have so enriched one of America's foremost art forms, the 
motion picture," said the college's acting president, James L. Doti, adding 
that the director and actor were being honored together because "so many of 
their greatest achievements are the films they made together." 
</P>
